<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,564,1165]" pageId="7" pageNumber="509">
Redescription: Body length: about 
<quantity box="[588,675,672,696]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="509" unit="mm" value="8.2">8.2 mm</quantity>
, wing length: about 
<quantity box="[901,990,672,697]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="509" unit="mm" value="7.6">7.6 mm</quantity>
; this species is generally glossy black in the ground colour, without any white scale bands on thorax and abdomen; frons and face with numerous black hairs and few yellowish-white scales; scape and pedicel black, flagellum conical, dark brown with the second flagellomere light brown; scutum with short black hairs especially on the back, and long yellowish-white hairs at margins, with collar longer and darker; scutellar bristles weak, yellowish-white; wings hyaline, with faint yellowish-brown basicostal infuscation tending to be more intense on basal costal cell, subcostal cell, and the basal area below the stem vein; legs blackish-brown to black covered with sparse whitish scales; abdomen with sparse yellowish-white scales especially on sides of tergites 3–7; tergite 1 with long white hairs at sides, becoming shorter and mixed with black ones at sides of tergites 2–7; abdominal tergites 4–7 with some long black hairs at the posterior margins. For hypopygium illustration, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Francois" box="[734,914,996,1021]" pageId="7" pageNumber="509" refString="Francois, F. J. J. (1970) Bombyliidae (Diptera) palearctiques du Musee Zoologique de Munich. Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royal d'Entomologie de Belgique, 106, 189 - 202." type="journal article" year="1970">François (1970)</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Francois" authorityYear="1970" box="[956,1234,996,1021]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Thyridanthrax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arabicola">
<emphasis box="[956,1234,996,1021]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="509">Thyridanthrax arabicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
